        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>197 Seventh Av<lb/>
                19&#47;7&#47;82<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S Morais<lb/>
                My dear sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Thanks for your<lb/> note.  I will send you Herald if anything<lb/> appears.  I will see what can be done in re<lb/> Luzzatto&#44; and will write to Montreal about your<lb/> Bible.  My uncle&#39;s library is willed to the son<lb/> succeeding to the ministry and Meldola&#44; the<lb/> oldest&#44; who has recently been elected will have it.<lb/>  Be&#91;&#63;&#93; is Jacob Cohen who has been re<lb/>commended to go to Philada.  If he cannot<lb/> pick up a living there he will try to return to<lb/> London.  Any attention in the way of passing<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>him forward would be appreciated<lb/> as he seems to be a good natured sort<lb/> of rolling stone.<lb/></p>
            <p>Vy try yrs<lb/>
                H P Mendes<lb/></p>
                
            <p>D. deSola Mendes is my younger<lb/> brother&#44; he has started a diamond<lb/> polishing factory.  Are there any<lb/> jewellers in your cong. who do business<lb/> in diamonds&#63; If so he would do their repair<lb/> work<lb/></p>
        </body>
